headline: Carrier Global (CARR): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Since June 2024, Carrier Global has been in a holding pattern, posting a small return of 3.4% while floating around $66.39. This is close to the S&P 500’s 6.1% gain during that period.
